What a FEELING! 
Here is my segment from the The Jennifer Hudson Show!
For them to feature me and my non profit The Art of Confidence Project is truly nothing short of amazing. 
Thank you to all who have supported me Jermaine Horton Studios in creating my passion project that has truly helped children all across the country. 
You can help us continue to help these amazing children by donating to our cause right on the website at the bottom. 
Thank you again! 
www.TheArtOfConfidence.org

It’s been a while since I laughed and smiled like this … I want to get back to him … 41 yrs around the sun and hopping to live each day like it’s my last going forward. Lot of pain and hurt through the years but each day I’m thankful for another day above ground!
I’m not going to make a cash app post but please if you want to get me something , consider donating to my non profit @theartofconfidenceproject on our website at the bottom so u can keep other amazing children around the country happy. Thank yawl!!!
Oh and I’m going to take more photos to have and post of my happiness moving forward.  @derrelhoshingportraits thanks for this old ass pic now 😂 
@mrblakemartin It’s time bro for some photos 📸

Special $100 an hour rate for rest of the 2023. 
Share and tag someone ❤️

@thestudio_28 
www.TheStudio28.com 

Reasons To Start a Podcast according to @forbes . 

There are a number of great reasons to start a podcast, the most common of which include:

1. You want to build an audience. 
The most successful podcasts reach millions of listeners. A podcast is a relatively inexpensive way to build a following.

2. You want to build credibility as an expert in your niche or industry.

3. You want another stream of revenue or income. Because podcasts are a more intimate medium, they can be a powerful way to sell your product or service. If you don’t have a specific product or service you’d like to sell, you may 
eventually be able to monetize your podcast by playing sponsored advertisements and earn money that way.

4. You want to build your network. Through podcasting, you can meet other people who are interested in what you talk about and can help you further your career or business.

5. You want to have fun. You don’t have to have a particular business or monetization goal in mind to start a podcast. You can record a podcast purely for your own enjoyment.
